text: The United States presidential election in Delaware, 1968 was held on November 5, 1968. Delaware voters chose three representatives, or electors to the Electoral College, who voted for president and vice president. Republican former Vice President Richard Nixon won the state by 7,529 votes over Democratic incumbent Vice President Hubert Humphrey.
